1
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:51,000
-== 派拉蒙电影公司 1972年出品 ==-

2
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:04,000
-== 教父 第一部 ==-

3
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:04,000
-== The Godfather Part I  ==-

4
00:01:16,564 --> 00:01:18,532
我相信美国

5
00:01:16,632 --> 00:01:19,465
I believe in America.

6
00:01:19,601 --> 00:01:21,831
美国使我发了财

7
00:01:19,601 --> 00:01:22,536
America has made my fortune.

8
00:01:22,671 --> 00:01:26,732
And I raised my daughter in the American fashion.

9
00:01:22,737 --> 00:01:25,535
而我以美国方式教养我的女儿

10
00:01:26,841 --> 00:01:28,866
我给她自由

11
00:01:26,875 --> 00:01:31,608
I gave her freedom, but I taught her never to dishonour her family.

12
00:01:29,010 --> 00:01:31,843
但也告诉她永远不要有辱家门

13
00:01:33,081 --> 00:01:36,141
She found a boyfriend, not an Italian.

14
00:01:33,114 --> 00:01:36,140
她交了位男友但不是意大利人

15
00:01:36,285 --> 00:01:40,779
She went to the movies with him. She stayed out late.

16
00:01:36,351 --> 00:01:40,481
她跟他去看电影，深夜才回家

17
00:01:40,889 --> 00:01:42,914
我并没有责骂她

18
00:01:40,923 --> 00:01:42,618
I didn't protest.

19
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:46,651
两个月前他与另一个男孩

20
00:01:43,625 --> 00:01:48,358
Two months ago he took her for a drive with another boyfriend.

21
00:01:46,828 --> 00:01:48,557
带她去兜风

22
00:01:49,364 --> 00:01:52,026
They made her drink whiskey

23
00:01:49,397 --> 00:01:51,592
他们强灌她喝威士忌

24
00:01:52,133 --> 00:01:56,001
然后他们想要占她便宜

25
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:56,399
and then they tried to take advantage of her.

26
00:01:56,538 --> 00:02:00,838
She resisted, she kept her honour.

27
00:01:56,604 --> 00:02:00,938
她抵抗，她保住了名节

28
00:02:01,976 --> 00:02:05,412
于是他们像对动物般的毒打她

29
00:02:01,977 --> 00:02:05,743
So they beat her like an animal.

30
00:02:06,915 --> 00:02:11,818
When I went to the hospital, her nose was broken,

31
00:02:06,981 --> 00:02:08,812
当我到医院时

32
00:02:09,150 --> 00:02:11,175
她的鼻梁断了

33
00:02:11,920 --> 00:02:13,911
她的下巴被打碎了

34
00:02:11,954 --> 00:02:16,687
her jaw was shattered, held together by wire.

35
00:02:14,022 --> 00:02:16,752
必须用钢丝绑着才不会掉下来

36
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:21,961
She couldn't even weep because of the pain.

37
00:02:18,593 --> 00:02:21,756
她痛得不能哭

38
00:02:24,066 --> 00:02:27,627
But I wept. Why did I weep?

39
00:02:24,099 --> 00:02:27,933
但我却哭了，我为什么哭呢？

40
00:02:30,172 --> 00:02:32,970
She was the light of my life.

41
00:02:30,238 --> 00:02:33,105
我视她如珠如宝

42
00:02:34,543 --> 00:02:36,272
Beautiful girl.

43
00:02:34,642 --> 00:02:36,269
长得很美丽

44
00:02:40,015 --> 00:02:42,950
Now she will never be beautiful again.

45
00:02:40,048 --> 00:02:42,676
现在她再也美丽不起来

46
00:02:49,558 --> 00:02:51,549
Sorry.

47
00:02:49,724 --> 00:02:50,782
不好意思

48
00:02:59,134 --> 00:03:03,730
I went to the police, like a good American.

49
00:02:59,167 --> 00:03:01,192
我…像个守法的美国人一样

50
00:03:01,369 --> 00:03:03,132
我去报警

51
00:03:03,872 --> 00:03:06,534
These two boys were brought to trial.

52
00:03:03,905 --> 00:03:06,169
那两个男孩受到了审判

53
00:03:07,642 --> 00:03:12,579
法官判他们有期徒刑三年 但缓刑

54
00:03:07,643 --> 00:03:12,706
The judge sentenced them to three years in prison, but suspended the sentence.

55
00:03:13,782 --> 00:03:19,084
Suspended the sentence! They went free that very day!

56
00:03:13,848 --> 00:03:16,214
缓刑！

57
00:03:16,551 --> 00:03:19,349
他们当天就没事了！

58
00:03:21,089 --> 00:03:24,354
I stood in the courtroom like a fool.

59
00:03:21,122 --> 00:03:24,114
我像个傻瓜似的站在法庭中

60
00:03:24,493 --> 00:03:28,224
Those two bastards, they smiled at me.

61
00:03:24,592 --> 00:03:28,187
而那两个混蛋竟朝着我笑

62
00:03:29,264 --> 00:03:35,225
Then I said to my wife, "For justice, we must go to Don Corleone."

63
00:03:29,297 --> 00:03:30,764
于是我对我太太说

64
00:03:30,865 --> 00:03:35,461
为求公道 我们必须去找柯里昂阁下

65
00:03:40,241 --> 00:03:43,677
你去报警前为何不先来找我？

66
00:03:40,242 --> 00:03:44,542
Why did you go to the police? Why didn't you come to me first?

67
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:50,778
What do you want of me? Tell me anything, but do what I beg you to do.

68
00:03:44,813 --> 00:03:46,337
你要我怎么样？

69
00:03:46,614 --> 00:03:50,209
你尽管吩咐 但求你一定要帮我这个忙

70
00:03:50,919 --> 00:03:52,580
What is that?

71
00:03:51,019 --> 00:03:52,247
帮你什么忙？

72
00:04:03,532 --> 00:04:05,363
I want them dead.

73
00:04:17,212 --> 00:04:18,543
That I cannot do.

74
00:04:17,245 --> 00:04:18,712
那个我办不到

75
00:04:20,282 --> 00:04:22,773
I'll give you anything you ask.

76
00:04:20,381 --> 00:04:22,781
你要什么，我都会给你

77
00:04:25,120 --> 00:04:30,683
I've known you many years, but this is the first time you've asked for help.

78
00:04:25,220 --> 00:04:26,847
我们相识多年

79
00:04:27,021 --> 00:04:30,422
这是你第一次来找我帮忙

80
00:04:31,693 --> 00:04:37,029
I can't remember the last time you invited me for a cup of coffee.

81
00:04:31,759 --> 00:04:36,594
我记不起你上次是何时 请我到你家去喝咖啡了

82
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:41,797
Even though my wife is godmother to your only child.

83
00:04:38,132 --> 00:04:41,329
何况我太太 还是你独生女的教母

84
00:04:41,937 --> 00:04:46,874
But let's be frank here. You never wanted my friendship.

85
00:04:42,036 --> 00:04:44,004
我坦白说吧！

86
00:04:44,272 --> 00:04:46,263
你从来就不想要我的友谊

87
00:04:47,009 --> 00:04:50,740
And you were afraid to be in my debt.

88
00:04:47,108 --> 00:04:50,771
而且你怕欠我人情

89
00:04:50,879 --> 00:04:53,313
I didn't want to get into trouble.

90
00:04:51,012 --> 00:04:53,173
我不想卷入是非

91
00:04:54,416 --> 00:04:57,180
I understand.

92
00:04:54,449 --> 00:04:55,882
我了解

93
00:04:57,319 --> 00:05:00,220
You found Paradise in America.

94
00:04:57,385 --> 00:04:59,945
你在美国发了财

95
00:05:02,524 --> 00:05:07,325
You made a good living, had police protection and there were courts of law.

96
00:05:02,724 --> 00:05:04,351
生意做的很好，生活过的很好

97
00:05:04,459 --> 00:05:07,428
有警察和法律保护你

98
00:05:07,462 --> 00:05:10,158
You didn't need a friend like me.

99
00:05:07,562 --> 00:05:09,621
你不需要我这种朋友

100
00:05:11,800 --> 00:05:15,292
But now you come to me and say,

101
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,198
但是…

102
00:05:13,368 --> 00:05:15,165
现在你来找我说

103
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:17,738
柯里昂阁下，请帮我主持公道

104
00:05:15,437 --> 00:05:18,270
"Don Corleone, give me justice."

105
00:05:19,675 --> 00:05:22,542
But you don't ask with respect.

106
00:05:19,774 --> 00:05:22,038
但你对我一点尊重也没有

107
00:05:22,678 --> 00:05:28,116
You don't offer friendship. You don't even think to call me Godfather.

108
00:05:22,744 --> 00:05:24,609
你并不把我当朋友

109
00:05:25,446 --> 00:05:27,744
你甚至不愿意喊我教父

110
00:05:29,151 --> 00:05:36,057
You come on my daughter's wedding day and ask me to murder for money.

111
00:05:29,284 --> 00:05:32,583
你在我女儿结婚当天来我家

112
00:05:32,754 --> 00:05:35,780
用钱收买我为你杀人

113
00:05:35,990 --> 00:05:38,424
我只是要求你主持公道

114
00:05:36,191 --> 00:05:38,682
I ask you for justice.

115
00:05:38,793 --> 00:05:41,591
那不是公道，你女儿还活着

116
00:05:38,827 --> 00:05:41,625
That is not justice. Your daughter is alive.

117
00:05:42,731 --> 00:05:46,599
Let them suffer, then, as she suffers.

118
00:05:42,764 --> 00:05:46,564
那么让他们像她一样受折磨

119
00:05:48,303 --> 00:05:49,861
我应该付你多少钱？

120
00:05:48,303 --> 00:05:50,601
How much shall I pay you?

121
00:06:05,219 --> 00:06:06,777
包纳萨拉

122
00:06:05,287 --> 00:06:09,223
Bonasera, Bonasera.

123
00:06:07,722 --> 00:06:08,950
包纳萨拉

124
00:06:09,157 --> 00:06:10,454
到底我做了什么

125
00:06:09,357 --> 00:06:13,418
What have I ever done to make you treat me so disrespectfully?

126
00:06:10,558 --> 00:06:13,118
让你这么的不尊重我

127
00:06:14,463 --> 00:06:17,057
If you'd come in friendship,

128
00:06:14,562 --> 00:06:16,689
如果你以朋友身分来找我

129
00:06:17,199 --> 00:06:21,602
the scum that ruined your daughter would be suffering this very day.

130
00:06:17,231 --> 00:06:21,531
那么伤害你女儿的杂碎 就会受到折磨

131
00:06:22,704 --> 00:06:28,040
And if an honest man like you should make enemies, they'd be my enemies.

132
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:24,499
你这种诚实人的敌人

133
00:06:24,639 --> 00:06:28,200
也就是我的敌人

134
00:06:30,879 --> 00:06:33,712
And then they would fear you.

135
00:06:30,945 --> 00:06:33,072
那么，他们就会怕你

136
00:06:37,252 --> 00:06:39,345
Be my friend?

137
00:06:37,285 --> 00:06:38,650
当我的朋友？

138
00:06:43,225 --> 00:06:45,284
Godfather?

139
00:06:43,424 --> 00:06:44,755
教父

140
00:06:49,197 --> 00:06:50,391
Good.

141
00:06:49,330 --> 00:06:50,354
很好

142
00:06:52,434 --> 00:06:57,633
Some day, and that day may never come, I'll ask a service of you.

143
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:54,627
他日我或需要你的帮忙

144
00:06:54,736 --> 00:06:57,102
也可能不会有那么一天

145
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:01,201
But until that day...

146
00:06:59,073 --> 00:07:01,769
但在那一天到来之前

147
00:07:02,844 --> 00:07:07,144
...accept this justice as a gift on my daughter's wedding day.

148
00:07:02,944 --> 00:07:06,277
收下这份公道 做为小女结婚之礼

149
00:07:07,282 --> 00:07:09,842
- Grazie, Godfather. - Prego.

150
00:07:07,348 --> 00:07:09,714
-谢谢，教父 -别客气

151
00:07:16,290 --> 00:07:19,987
这件事交给…克里曼沙

152
00:07:16,825 --> 00:07:19,794
Give this to Clemenza.

153
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:25,322
I want people that aren't going to get carried away.

154
00:07:21,863 --> 00:07:25,355
我要用可靠的人 头脑清醒的人

155
00:07:25,467 --> 00:07:29,631
We're not murderers, in spite of what this undertaker says.

156
00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:29,493
我们不是谋杀犯，下手别太重

157
00:07:54,863 --> 00:07:58,299
- Where's Michael? - Don't worry, he'll be here.

158
00:07:54,962 --> 00:07:57,760
-麦克在哪？ -别担心，他一会就来

159
00:07:59,333 --> 00:08:01,699
没有麦克我不照相

160
00:07:59,501 --> 00:08:02,231
We're not taking the picture without Michael.

161
00:08:02,704 --> 00:08:06,265
待会再拍

162
00:08:08,844 --> 00:08:11,574
- What's the matter? - It's Michael.

163
00:08:08,910 --> 00:08:10,707
-什么事？ -麦克的事

164
00:09:00,962 --> 00:09:02,623
Don Barzini.

165
00:09:01,062 --> 00:09:02,495
你好，巴西尼阁下

166
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:08,065
你认得我儿子吧？

167
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:22,013
保利，让我喝点酒

168
00:09:19,180 --> 00:09:22,308
Hey, Paulie! Let me have some wine.

169
00:09:22,350 --> 00:09:24,784
保利，再来点酒

170
00:09:22,450 --> 00:09:24,680
Paulie! More wine.

171
00:09:26,388 --> 00:09:31,792
- You look terrific on the floor. - Are you a dance judge or something?

172
00:09:26,521 --> 00:09:29,718
-你看起来棒极了 -你是裁判还是什么？

173
00:09:30,057 --> 00:09:33,959
闪开吧，到附近晃晃 做你的工作

174
00:09:31,927 --> 00:09:33,986
Take a walk and do your job.

175
00:09:41,770 --> 00:09:45,035
Sandra, watch the kids. Don't let them run wild.

176
00:09:41,836 --> 00:09:44,669
仙杜拉，帮个忙 别让孩子乱跑，好吗？

177
00:09:44,839 --> 00:09:46,773
你看好你自己，好吗？

178
00:09:45,173 --> 00:09:48,108
You watch yourself, all right?

179
00:10:08,897 --> 00:10:12,958
20, 30 grand. In small bills, cash.

180
00:10:08,930 --> 00:10:13,230
两三万元小钞，全是现金

181
00:10:13,935 --> 00:10:16,062
In that little silk purse.

182
00:10:14,001 --> 00:10:16,231
全在那个小丝袋里

183
00:10:16,204 --> 00:10:19,970
If this were somebody else's wedding... Sfortunato!

184
00:10:16,470 --> 00:10:19,962
如果这是我的婚礼我就发财了

185
00:10:20,108 --> 00:10:22,508
Hey, Paulie!

186
00:10:20,141 --> 00:10:24,601
保利，接住吧！

187
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,474
Stupid jerk!

188
00:10:25,546 --> 00:10:26,638
你这个笨蛋！

189
00:10:35,490 --> 00:10:37,424
What's the matter?

190
00:10:35,556 --> 00:10:36,750
怎么回事？

191
00:10:49,838 --> 00:10:52,204
- Have to go back to work. - Tom.

192
00:10:49,904 --> 00:10:52,168
-我得回去工作了 -汤姆

193
00:10:52,273 --> 00:10:53,365
这是婚礼的一部分

194
00:10:52,340 --> 00:10:56,572
No Sicilian can refuse any request on his daughter's wedding day.

195
00:10:53,474 --> 00:10:56,307
没有西西里人在女儿结婚那天 能拒绝任何的请求

196
00:11:02,083 --> 00:11:07,419
柯里昂阁下 能受邀到贵府深感荣幸

197
00:11:02,317 --> 00:11:07,448
Don Corleone, I'm honoured and grateful that you have invited me.

198
00:11:10,258 --> 00:11:13,227
你们在干什么？滚！

199
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:15,557
Get out of here! It's a private party. Go on!

200
00:11:13,628 --> 00:11:15,255
这是私人宴会，快滚

201
00:11:16,564 --> 00:11:19,533
What is it? It's my sister's wedding.

202
00:11:16,664 --> 00:11:19,326
这算什么？是我妹妹的婚礼

203
00:11:26,141 --> 00:11:29,406
Goddamn FBI don't respect nothing!

204
00:11:26,207 --> 00:11:28,801
该死的联邦密探什么都不尊重

205
00:11:31,846 --> 00:11:34,440
Come here, come here, come here!

206
00:11:31,946 --> 00:11:35,507
过来这！…

207
00:11:49,330 --> 00:11:53,960
...but towards the end, he was paroled to help with the American war effort,

208
00:11:49,363 --> 00:11:53,925
但最后他获假释去为美国作战

209
00:11:54,035 --> 00:11:56,629
过去六个月 他在我的糕饼店做事

210
00:11:54,102 --> 00:11:57,128
so for six months he's worked in my pastry shop.

211
00:11:57,272 --> 00:11:59,968
Nazorine, what can I do for you?

212
00:11:57,305 --> 00:11:59,466
纳色利，我的朋友 我能为你做什么？

213
00:12:00,041 --> 00:12:01,804
现在战争结束了

214
00:12:00,108 --> 00:12:02,042
Now that the war is over,

215
00:12:02,009 --> 00:12:05,410
这男孩，安索 他们要把他遣返意大利

216
00:12:02,177 --> 00:12:06,079
this boy, Enzo, they want to repatriate him back to Italy.

217
00:12:06,214 --> 00:12:11,242
Godfather, I have a daughter. You see, she and Enzo...

218
00:12:06,247 --> 00:12:11,514
教父，我有个女儿 她和安索…

219
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:16,814
You want Enzo to stay in this country, and your daughter to be married.

220
00:12:12,420 --> 00:12:16,356
你要安索留在这个国家 和你女儿成亲

221
00:12:17,925 --> 00:12:20,450
你什么都了解，谢谢

222
00:12:17,959 --> 00:12:20,223
You understand everything.

223
00:12:21,129 --> 00:12:23,495
Mr Hagen. Thank you.

224
00:12:21,228 --> 00:12:23,662
哈金先生，谢谢

225
00:12:26,634 --> 00:12:29,432
待会看看我为你女儿 做的结婚蛋糕

226
00:12:26,835 --> 00:12:30,566
Wait till you see the wedding cake I made for your daughter!

227
00:12:29,603 --> 00:12:32,834
这么高…还有一对新人和天使

228
00:12:30,705 --> 00:12:33,469
The bride, the groom and the angel...

229
00:12:38,646 --> 00:12:43,140
- Who should I give this job to? - Not to our paisa.

230
00:12:38,779 --> 00:12:40,474
这件事我该交给谁去办？

231
00:12:40,648 --> 00:12:42,275
别给我们这个选区

232
00:12:43,284 --> 00:12:48,586
Give it to a Jew Congressman in another district. Who else is on the list?

233
00:12:43,451 --> 00:12:46,318
给别地区的犹太籍众议员

234
00:12:47,421 --> 00:12:48,718
名单上还有谁？

235
00:12:54,595 --> 00:12:57,029
你好！麦克！

236
00:12:55,597 --> 00:12:57,189
Hey, Michael!

237
00:13:16,951 --> 00:13:20,387
He's not on the list, but Luca Brasi wants to see you.

238
00:13:17,018 --> 00:13:19,748
路卡布拉西不在名单上 但他想要见你

239
00:13:26,161 --> 00:13:28,493
Is this necessary?

240
00:13:26,260 --> 00:13:28,728
这个…有这个必要吗？

241
00:13:28,630 --> 00:13:33,192
He didn't expect to be invited to the wedding, so he wanted to thank you.

242
00:13:28,829 --> 00:13:31,957
他没料到会受邀参加婚礼 所以要向你致谢

243
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:33,898
好吧

244
00:13:34,602 --> 00:13:39,869
柯里昂阁下，在令媛婚礼这天

245
00:13:34,669 --> 00:13:40,266
Don Corleone, I'm honoured and grateful that you have invited me

246
00:13:40,274 --> 00:13:42,367
能受邀到贵府深感荣幸

247
00:13:40,408 --> 00:13:45,641
on the wedding day of your daughter. May their first child be a masculine child.

248
00:13:43,010 --> 00:13:45,706
希望他们早生贵子

249
00:13:46,714 --> 00:13:47,976
麦克！

250
00:13:46,714 --> 00:13:48,147
Michael...

251
00:13:49,884 --> 00:13:52,250
那边的那个人在自言自语

252
00:13:49,951 --> 00:13:53,114
That man over there is talking to himself.

253
00:13:53,254 --> 00:13:56,314
See that scary guy over there?

254
00:13:53,354 --> 00:13:55,788
看到那边 那个吓人的砘锪寺穑

255
00:13:56,457 --> 00:13:59,893
- He's a very scary guy. - What's his name?

256
00:13:56,490 --> 00:13:59,618
-他很叫人害怕 -他是谁？叫什么名字？

257
00:14:00,028 --> 00:14:04,465
His name is Luca Brasi. He helps my father out sometimes.

258
00:14:00,061 --> 00:14:04,725
他叫做路卡布拉西 有时候替家父办事

259
00:14:05,833 --> 00:14:08,734
Michael, he's coming over here!

260
00:14:06,367 --> 00:14:08,232
麦克！等一下，他过来了

261
00:14:08,335 --> 00:14:09,666
麦克！

262
00:14:11,205 --> 00:14:12,570
汤姆！

263
00:14:13,575 --> 00:14:15,406
You look terrific!

264
00:14:13,641 --> 00:14:15,074
你气色好极了！

265
00:14:15,543 --> 00:14:17,477
家兄汤姆哈金，这是凯亚当斯

266
00:14:15,543 --> 00:14:18,808
My brother Tom Hagen, Miss Kay Adams.

267
00:14:17,645 --> 00:14:18,976
-你好 -你好

268
00:14:20,247 --> 00:14:22,215
你父亲要见你

269
00:14:20,448 --> 00:14:22,746
Your father's been asking for you.

270
00:14:22,884 --> 00:14:25,717
- Very nice to meet you. - Nice to meet you.

271
00:14:23,217 --> 00:14:24,741
-幸会！ -幸会

272
00:14:27,522 --> 00:14:30,150
Why does your brother have a different name?

273
00:14:27,655 --> 00:14:29,680
若他是你哥哥，为何不同姓？

274
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:35,695
小时候在街上 发现汤姆无家可归

275
00:14:30,291 --> 00:14:33,954
My brother Sonny found Tom Hagen in the street.

276
00:14:34,095 --> 00:14:38,691
He had no home, so my father took him in.

277
00:14:36,564 --> 00:14:38,259
所以家父收养了他

278
00:14:39,934 --> 00:14:42,835
He's been with us ever since.

279
00:14:39,967 --> 00:14:41,559
从此他就和我们住在一起了

280
00:14:42,971 --> 00:14:44,939
He's a good lawyer.

281
00:14:43,170 --> 00:14:44,432
他是个好律师

282
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:50,140
不是西西里人 但我想他会当军师

283
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:50,434
Not a Sicilian. I think he's going to be consigliere.

284
00:14:50,578 --> 00:14:53,479
- What's that? - That's a...

285
00:14:50,644 --> 00:14:52,703
-那是什么？ -那是…

286
00:14:53,615 --> 00:14:57,244
...like a counsellor, an advisor. Very important for the family.

287
00:14:53,647 --> 00:14:56,741
像是个顾问 在家族中的地位非常重要

288
00:14:58,353 --> 00:15:00,480
You like your lasagne?

289
00:14:58,385 --> 00:15:00,250
你的扁形通心面还好吧？

290
00:15:04,825 --> 00:15:06,258
柯里昂阁下

291
00:15:04,826 --> 00:15:06,987
Don Corleone.

292
00:15:07,094 --> 00:15:11,030
在令媛的婚礼受到邀请

293
00:15:07,128 --> 00:15:09,619
I'm honoured and grateful

294
00:15:09,764 --> 00:15:13,723
that you have invited me to your daughter's wedding.

295
00:15:11,132 --> 00:15:14,067
深感荣幸与感激

296
00:15:18,706 --> 00:15:21,834
On the day of your daughter's wedding.

297
00:15:18,739 --> 00:15:21,264
在令媛结婚的当天

298
00:15:21,976 --> 00:15:27,209
And I hope that their first child will be a masculine child.

299
00:15:22,042 --> 00:15:27,412
我希望他们能早生贵子

300
00:15:28,316 --> 00:15:33,720
I pledge my ever-ending loyalty.

301
00:15:28,349 --> 00:15:34,515
这是我一点小小的心意

302
00:15:35,422 --> 00:15:38,391
-祝福他们俩白头偕老 -谢谢你，路卡

303
00:15:35,423 --> 00:15:40,383
- For your daughter's bridal purse. - Thank you, Luca. Most valued friend.

304
00:15:38,492 --> 00:15:40,426
我最珍贵的朋友

305
00:15:40,895 --> 00:15:46,026
Don Corleone, I'm going to leave you now, because I know you're busy.

306
00:15:40,928 --> 00:15:45,956
柯里昂阁下，我晓得你忙 我先告退了

307
00:15:46,601 --> 00:15:47,966
Thank you.

308
00:15:46,734 --> 00:15:47,826
谢谢

309
00:16:37,585 --> 00:16:39,917
Signora Corleone!

310
00:16:37,818 --> 00:16:39,251
柯里昂夫人

311
00:16:40,054 --> 00:16:42,113
No!

312
00:16:41,121 --> 00:16:44,818
不！…

313
00:17:52,927 --> 00:17:57,955
Senator Cauley apologised for not coming, but said you'd understand.

314
00:17:53,060 --> 00:17:55,551
科利参议员对不能亲自来致歉

315
00:17:55,729 --> 00:17:56,957
他说你会谅解的

316
00:17:58,099 --> 00:18:02,331
Also some of the judges. They've all sent gifts.

317
00:17:58,165 --> 00:18:02,295
还有一些法官也一样 他们都送了礼物

318
00:18:03,837 --> 00:18:04,826
敬你！

319
00:18:05,373 --> 00:18:06,670
What is that outside?

320
00:18:05,472 --> 00:18:06,734
外面是怎么回事？

321
00:18:15,416 --> 00:18:20,149
强尼！…

322
00:18:15,716 --> 00:18:18,685
Johnny! Johnny!

323
00:18:21,322 --> 00:18:22,983
I love you!

324
00:18:21,355 --> 00:18:23,016
我爱你！

325
00:18:33,067 --> 00:18:35,535
他大老远由加州赶来参加婚礼

326
00:18:33,134 --> 00:18:36,661
He came all the way from California. I told you he'd come!

327
00:18:35,669 --> 00:18:36,693
我告诉过你他会来的

328
00:18:36,804 --> 00:18:38,795
已经两年了，他也许又有麻烦

329
00:18:36,804 --> 00:18:40,296
- He's probably in trouble again. - He's a good godson.

330
00:18:38,906 --> 00:18:40,168
他是个好教子

331
00:18:41,142 --> 00:18:45,806
Johnny, Johnny! Sing a song!

332
00:18:41,375 --> 00:18:45,971
强尼！…唱首歌

333
00:19:01,128 --> 00:19:04,029
You never said you knew Johnny Fontane!

334
00:19:01,295 --> 00:19:03,991
麦克！你从未告诉我 你认得强尼方亭

335
00:19:04,164 --> 00:19:07,998
-你想见他吗？ -当然！

336
00:19:04,165 --> 00:19:08,101
- Sure. You want to meet him? - Great! Sure.

337
00:19:08,236 --> 00:19:12,138
- My father helped him with his career. - He did?

338
00:19:08,402 --> 00:19:11,394
-家父帮他建立他的事业 -真的？

339
00:19:12,273 --> 00:19:13,365
How?

340
00:19:12,306 --> 00:19:13,330
怎么做的？

341
00:19:15,376 --> 00:19:17,776
- Let's listen to this song. - Michael...

342
00:19:15,442 --> 00:19:17,501
-我们先听这首唱 -不，麦克

343
00:19:51,879 --> 00:19:54,040
Please, Michael. Tell me.

344
00:19:51,912 --> 00:19:54,107
拜托，麦克！告诉我

345
00:19:57,852 --> 00:20:02,687
When Johnny was starting out, he was signed to a personal service contract

346
00:19:57,918 --> 00:20:04,118
强尼刚出道时 和一个乐队领班签了合约

347
00:20:02,823 --> 00:20:05,656
with a big bandleader.

348
00:20:05,726 --> 00:20:09,287
当他走红后，想要解除合约

349
00:20:05,793 --> 00:20:10,924
And as his career got better and better, he wanted to get out of it.

350
00:20:11,031 --> 00:20:13,226
强尼是家父的教子

351
00:20:11,065 --> 00:20:13,556
Johnny is my father's godson.

352
00:20:13,701 --> 00:20:17,137
My father went to see this bandleader.

353
00:20:14,668 --> 00:20:16,761
于是家父去见乐队负责人

354
00:20:17,271 --> 00:20:21,105
He offered him 10,000 dollars to let Johnny go,

355
00:20:17,371 --> 00:20:20,067
而且出一万元要他与强尼解约

356
00:20:21,242 --> 00:20:23,904
but the bandleader said no.

357
00:20:21,375 --> 00:20:23,036
他说不行！

358
00:20:24,045 --> 00:20:29,415
So the next day my father went to see him, but this time with Luca Brasi.

359
00:20:24,178 --> 00:20:29,616
第二天家父再去见他 只是这次带着路卡布拉西

360
00:20:31,352 --> 00:20:33,513
Within an hour,

361
00:20:31,485 --> 00:20:32,884
一个小时之内

362
00:20:33,654 --> 00:20:39,422
he signed a release for a certified cheque of 1,000 dollars.

363
00:20:33,754 --> 00:20:39,454
他签了解约书 只收了一千元的支票

364
00:20:41,028 --> 00:20:44,828
- How did he do that? - Made him an offer he couldn't refuse.

365
00:20:41,128 --> 00:20:42,254
他是怎么办到的？

366
00:20:42,930 --> 00:20:45,125
家父提了个他不能拒绝的条件

367
00:20:46,567 --> 00:20:47,829
那是什么？

368
00:20:46,667 --> 00:20:51,536
- What was that? - Luca Brasi held a gun to his head,

369
00:20:48,869 --> 00:20:51,235
路卡布拉西用枪顶着他的头

370
00:20:51,672 --> 00:20:56,609
他要是不签字脑袋就会开花

371
00:20:51,672 --> 00:20:56,905
and father said that either his brains or his signature would be on the contract.

372
00:21:01,916 --> 00:21:03,611
That's a true story.

373
00:21:02,015 --> 00:21:03,380
这是真实的故事

374
00:21:14,862 --> 00:21:17,626
That's my family, Kay. It's not me.

375
00:21:15,062 --> 00:21:17,792
凯，那是我的家庭，不是我

376
00:21:30,144 --> 00:21:31,873
Beautiful!

377
00:22:04,211 --> 00:22:05,542
我会处理的

378
00:22:04,245 --> 00:22:06,213
I'll take care of it.

379
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:07,372
汤姆！

380
00:22:06,347 --> 00:22:08,212
Tom...

381
00:22:08,349 --> 00:22:11,944
I want you to find Santino. Tell him to come to the office.

382
00:22:08,682 --> 00:22:11,583
叫山提诺来我的办公室

383
00:22:19,260 --> 00:22:22,161
How are you, Fredo?

384
00:22:19,359 --> 00:22:20,826
你好吗？弗雷多

385
00:22:21,328 --> 00:22:24,627
-家兄弗雷多 -这位是凯亚当斯

386
00:22:22,296 --> 00:22:24,890
My brother Fredo, this is Kay Adams.

387
00:22:25,933 --> 00:22:28,401
- Hi. - How are you doing?

388
00:22:25,999 --> 00:22:27,864
-你好 -你好吗？

389
00:22:30,271 --> 00:22:34,674
- This is my brother Mike. - Are you having a good time?

390
00:22:30,404 --> 00:22:32,872
-这是舍弟麦克 -玩的愉快吗？

391
00:22:34,809 --> 00:22:37,277
Yeah. This is your friend?

392
00:22:34,875 --> 00:22:36,274
这是你的朋友？

393
00:22:37,411 --> 00:22:42,781
I don't know what to do. My voice is weak. It's weak.

394
00:22:37,778 --> 00:22:39,370
我不知道该怎么办

395
00:22:39,546 --> 00:22:42,447
我的嗓子很虚弱，很虚弱

396
00:22:43,884 --> 00:22:50,187
Anyway, if I had this part in the picture, it puts me right back on top again.

397
00:22:43,951 --> 00:22:47,352
总之我若能得到那部戏的角色

398
00:22:47,721 --> 00:22:49,882
我会再次走红的

399
00:22:50,324 --> 00:22:55,728
But this... man won't give it to me, the head of the studio.

400
00:22:50,490 --> 00:22:55,689
但是电影公司的老板不让我演

401
00:22:55,829 --> 00:22:58,730
-他叫什么名字？ -华尔斯

402
00:22:55,863 --> 00:22:58,957
- What's his name? - Woltz.

403
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:03,537
He won't give it to me, and he says there's no chance.

404
00:22:59,166 --> 00:23:03,626
他不肯让我演 而且还说门都没有

405
00:23:07,475 --> 00:23:08,772
Sonny?

406
00:23:07,708 --> 00:23:08,800
山尼？

407
00:23:10,411 --> 00:23:11,503
Sonny?

408
00:23:10,677 --> 00:23:11,701
山尼？

409
00:23:18,119 --> 00:23:19,211
Sonny?

410
00:23:18,251 --> 00:23:19,240
山尼？

411
00:23:20,187 --> 00:23:22,815
- Sonny, are you in there? - What?

412
00:23:20,220 --> 00:23:21,551
山尼？你在里面吗？

413
00:23:22,089 --> 00:23:23,078
什么事？

414
00:23:22,957 --> 00:23:24,481
The old man wants you.

415
00:23:23,156 --> 00:23:24,453
老头子要见你

416
00:23:26,126 --> 00:23:27,753
好，马上去

417
00:23:26,160 --> 00:23:27,855
One minute.

418
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,667
山尼

419
00:23:42,109 --> 00:23:43,337
一个月以前

420
00:23:42,343 --> 00:23:47,212
A month ago he bought the movie rights to this book, a best-seller.

421
00:23:43,510 --> 00:23:46,570
他买下这本畅销书的电影版权

422
00:23:47,348 --> 00:23:50,806
The main character is a guy just like me.

423
00:23:47,447 --> 00:23:50,541
男主角就像是我的写照

424
00:23:50,851 --> 00:23:53,752
我根本不需要演 只要当我自己即可

425
00:23:50,951 --> 00:23:53,613
I wouldn't even have to act.

426
00:23:54,488 --> 00:23:57,787
但…教父，我不知该怎么办？

427
00:23:54,722 --> 00:23:57,589
Godfather, I don't know what to do.

428
00:23:58,792 --> 00:24:00,885
你要表现得像个男人！

429
00:23:58,826 --> 00:24:03,126
You can act like a man! What's the matter with you?

430
00:24:00,994 --> 00:24:02,291
你是怎么回事？

431
00:24:03,230 --> 00:24:05,357
这就是你在好莱坞学到的？

432
00:24:03,264 --> 00:24:08,930
Is this how you turned out a Hollywood finocchio, that cries like a woman?

433
00:24:05,465 --> 00:24:07,558
哭的像个女人？

434
00:24:09,036 --> 00:24:11,596
该怎么办？怎么办？

435
00:24:09,069 --> 00:24:12,869
"What can I do? What can I do?" What is that nonsense?

436
00:24:11,705 --> 00:24:12,967
算什么鬼话？

437
00:24:13,007 --> 00:24:14,838
Ridiculous.

438
00:24:13,340 --> 00:24:14,500
岂有此理！

439
00:24:19,446 --> 00:24:22,643
- You spend time with your family? - Sure I do.

440
00:24:19,513 --> 00:24:22,539
-你有花时间与家人共聚吗？ -我当然有

441
00:24:22,783 --> 00:24:24,273
Good.

442
00:24:22,816 --> 00:24:23,805
很好

443
00:24:24,418 --> 00:24:29,685
Because a man who doesn't spend time with his family can never be a real man.

444
00:24:24,518 --> 00:24:28,181
因为不抽空陪家人的男人 不是真正的男人

445
00:24:28,922 --> 00:24:30,048
过来这

446
00:24:34,795 --> 00:24:38,231
You look terrible. I want you to eat.

447
00:24:34,861 --> 00:24:37,762
你看来糟透了，我要你多吃点

448
00:24:38,331 --> 00:24:39,320
好好休息

449
00:24:38,365 --> 00:24:43,598
Rest, and in a month this Hollywood big shot will give you what you want.

450
00:24:39,433 --> 00:24:43,335
从现在起一个月内 好莱坞大亨会让你愿望成真

451
00:24:43,737 --> 00:24:46,900
It's too late, they start shooting in a week.

452
00:24:43,804 --> 00:24:46,102
太迟了 他们一周内就要开拍了

453
00:24:47,041 --> 00:24:50,169
I'm going to make him an offer he can't refuse.

454
00:24:47,074 --> 00:24:49,736
我会给他一个 他无法拒绝的提议

455
00:24:52,879 --> 00:24:57,873
现在你到外面去好好的玩

456
00:24:53,013 --> 00:24:57,973
Just go outside and enjoy yourself, and forget about all this nonsense.

457
00:24:59,186 --> 00:25:03,646
-其他的交给我来办 -好的

458
00:25:00,454 --> 00:25:03,514
- I want you to leave it all to me. - All right.

459
00:25:28,315 --> 00:25:33,514
- What time does my daughter leave? - Soon, after they cut the cake.

460
00:25:28,348 --> 00:25:30,578
我女儿女婿何时离开？

461
00:25:31,318 --> 00:25:33,377
切完蛋糕后的几分钟

462
00:25:33,654 --> 00:25:37,021
Do we give your son-in-law something important?

463
00:25:33,720 --> 00:25:37,178
你的新女婿要给重要职务吗？

464
00:25:37,157 --> 00:25:42,527
Never. Give him a living, but never discuss the family business with him.

465
00:25:37,290 --> 00:25:38,621
永远不要！

466
00:25:38,792 --> 00:25:41,955
让他们过好日子 但别让他插手家族中的事

467
00:25:42,663 --> 00:25:45,461
- What else? - Virgil Sollozzo called.

468
00:25:42,863 --> 00:25:43,887
还有什么事？

469
00:25:43,997 --> 00:25:45,464
威尔斯索拉索来过电话

470
00:25:45,599 --> 00:25:50,036
- We'll have to see him next week. - When you come back from California.

471
00:25:45,632 --> 00:25:47,497
下周我们必须安排跟他见面

472
00:25:47,601 --> 00:25:50,126
等你从加州回来我们再讨论

473
00:25:51,472 --> 00:25:54,839
- When am I going to California? - Tonight.

474
00:25:51,505 --> 00:25:53,234
我何时要去加州了？

475
