572
00:31:01,081 --> 00:31:04,482
He never asks a second favour when he's been refused the first.

573
00:31:01,181 --> 00:31:04,480
他被拒绝一次后 不会再要求第二次

574
00:31:04,618 --> 00:31:10,648
You don't understand. Johnny Fontane never gets that movie.

575
00:31:04,651 --> 00:31:09,520
你不了解 强尼方亭永远别想演那部电影

576
00:31:10,791 --> 00:31:14,557
That part is perfect for him. It'll make him a big star.

577
00:31:10,924 --> 00:31:12,448
他很适合那个角色

578
00:31:12,625 --> 00:31:14,183
会让他成为巨星

579
00:31:14,694 --> 00:31:16,059
但我要让他走投无路

580
00:31:14,695 --> 00:31:18,461
I'm going to run him out of the business, and let me tell you why.

581
00:31:16,229 --> 00:31:18,094
我告诉你为什么

582
00:31:20,701 --> 00:31:25,400
Johnny Fontane ruined one of Woltz International's most valuable proteges.

583
00:31:20,867 --> 00:31:25,361
强尼毁了一位华尔斯国际公司 最有前途的女星

584
00:31:25,539 --> 00:31:30,875
We trained her for five years. Singing, acting, dancing lessons.

585
00:31:25,638 --> 00:31:27,731
五年来我们不断地训练她

586
00:31:27,841 --> 00:31:30,810
歌唱课、表演课、跳舞课

587
00:31:30,977 --> 00:31:33,172
我在她身上投资了无数的金钱

588
00:31:31,011 --> 00:31:35,573
I spent hundreds of thousands of dollars on her, to make her a big star.

589
00:31:33,279 --> 00:31:35,406
我要让她成为一位巨星

590
00:31:35,716 --> 00:31:38,378
Let me be even more frank.

591
00:31:35,748 --> 00:31:38,216
让我更坦白的告诉你

592
00:31:38,451 --> 00:31:43,388
让你知道我不是铁石心肠 也不是势利眼

593
00:31:38,518 --> 00:31:43,478
To show you that I'm not a hard-hearted man. That it's not all dollars and cents.

594
00:31:43,624 --> 00:31:47,185
She was beautiful. She was young and innocent!

595
00:31:43,723 --> 00:31:47,284
她年轻漂亮，天真无邪

596
00:31:47,327 --> 00:31:52,594
She's the greatest piece of ass I've had and I've had them all over the world.

597
00:31:47,427 --> 00:31:51,454
我拥有她就等于拥有全世界

598
00:31:52,733 --> 00:31:58,968
Then Johnny Fontane comes along with his olive oil voice and Guinea charm.

599
00:31:52,799 --> 00:31:55,927
然后强尼方亭出现了

600
00:31:56,035 --> 00:31:59,061
带着磁性的嗓音 加上意大利的魅力

601
00:31:59,106 --> 00:32:00,801
And she runs off.

602
00:31:59,239 --> 00:32:00,831
把她拐走了

603
00:32:02,108 --> 00:32:05,703
她跑掉了使我非常难堪

604
00:32:02,109 --> 00:32:05,135
She threw it all away just to make me look ridiculous!

605
00:32:06,312 --> 00:32:11,443
而我这种地位的人 无法忍受难堪

606
00:32:06,313 --> 00:32:11,478
And a man in my position can't afford to be made to look ridiculous!

607
00:32:11,618 --> 00:32:13,848
你马上给我滚

608
00:32:11,618 --> 00:32:13,848
You get the hell out of here!

609
00:32:13,987 --> 00:32:18,356
If that goombah tries any rough stuff, tell him I'm no bandleader.

610
00:32:14,020 --> 00:32:16,784
若是那混球想对我动粗

611
00:32:16,890 --> 00:32:18,858
你告诉他我不是乐队领班

612
00:32:19,593 --> 00:32:22,585
Yeah, I heard that story.

613
00:32:19,692 --> 00:32:22,820
我听过那个故事了

614
00:32:23,497 --> 00:32:27,365
Thank you for dinner and a very pleasant evening.

615
00:32:23,530 --> 00:32:25,521
谢谢你的晚餐款待

616
00:32:27,501 --> 00:32:30,231
Maybe your car can take me to the airport.

617
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:29,727
也许你能派车送我去机场

618
00:32:30,370 --> 00:32:34,136
Mr Corleone insists on hearing bad news immediately.

619
00:32:30,537 --> 00:32:33,802
柯里昂先生坚持 坏消息要立刻回报

620
00:34:26,753 --> 00:34:30,655
- You're not too tired, are you, Tom? - No, I slept on the plane.

621
00:34:26,786 --> 00:34:30,347
-你不会太累吧？汤姆 -我在飞机上睡过了

622
00:34:30,791 --> 00:34:33,760
I have the Sollozzo notes here.

623
00:34:30,857 --> 00:34:32,620
我这里有索拉索的资料

624
00:34:33,894 --> 00:34:35,156
Now...

625
00:34:34,060 --> 00:34:39,930
众人皆知，索拉索是土耳其人

626
00:34:37,264 --> 00:34:42,258
Sollozzo is known as The Turk. He's supposed to be very good with a knife,

627
00:34:40,767 --> 00:34:42,564
他应该善于用刀

628
00:34:42,936 --> 00:34:47,270
but only in matters of business with reasonable complaint.

629
00:34:42,969 --> 00:34:46,598
但只有发生利益冲突时 才会使用

630
00:34:47,407 --> 00:34:50,376
His business is narcotics.

631
00:34:47,473 --> 00:34:49,703
他是做毒品生意的

632
